

# TypeScript Learning Journey

I started learning TypeScript to write better, more reliable JavaScript. This repo is where I keep track of everything I learn вЂ” notes, code snippets, and small practice files.

Nothing fancy. Just consistent practice.

---

## Why TypeScript?

I got tired of runtime bugs that could have been caught earlier. TypeScript fixes that. It also makes code easier to read and refactor, especially as projects grow.

That's reason enough for me.

---

